eNCA speaks to Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is denying that government failed to protect consumers. The Competition Commission's health market inquiry found South Africans are paying exorbitant fees for private healthcare. WATCH: Ramaphosa 'pained' by corruption in healthcare sector It also found that the treatment offered is often unnecessary. Mkhize says government will introduce legislation to fix the health sector. WATCH: SA to finalise growth strategy 'within next few weeks': Ramaphosa "The private sector has to take the responsibility, the government has to take the responsibility and everyone else because we have to work on the basis of everyone collaborating to say what's the best way to protect consumers. There will be a lot of legislation that will be in place." Watch the full interview with Health Minister Zweli Mkhize above